New Gold, Silver Wheaton: Canadian Equity Market Preview

-- B y   J e n n i f e r   A .   J o h n s o n
-- 
2011-03-07T14:19:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-07/new-gold-silver-wheaton-canadian-equity-market-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Canadian trading.    New Gold Inc. (NGD)  : The gold producer was cut to
“market perform” from “buy” at Cormark Securities Inc. The
12-month price estimate is C$12.00.    Newalta Corp. (NAL)  : The industrial recycler was cut to
“market perform” from “buy” at Cormark Securities Inc. The
12-month price estimate is C$14.75.    Research In Motion Ltd. (RIM)  : The maker of the
Blackberry said Keith Pardy, its chief marketing officer, will
leave the company for personal reasons and will stay on for six
months to assist with a transition. His departure may have been
predicated on the perception that Research In Motion is losing a
public relations conflict with Google Inc.’s Android and Apple
Inc., JPMorgan Chase & Co. said.    Silver Wheaton Corp. (SLW)  : The silver producer was cut
to “sector perform” from “outperform” at Royal Bank of  Canada . The 12-month price estimate is C$48.00.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jennifer Johnson in New York at 
 jjohnson156@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Baker at   nbaker7@bloomberg.net . 